  "content:encoded": "<p> The principles of design can improve your life at work. Really.   Dave Evans is a lecturer at Stanford University’s design program and the co-author of “Designing Your New Work Life.” Before that, he was an early employee at Apple and a co-founder of Electronic Arts.  Producer Ricky Mulvey talks with Evans about:   - The power of creating a “good enough for now” mindset   - Deciding whether to quit or reinvent your job   - How to create more spontaneity in a hybrid-work environment   Stocks discussed: PINS, AAPL, HPQ     Host: Ricky Mulvey  Guests: Dave Evans  Engineers: Dan Boyd</p>",
